root: ^Morning, Zip. Looks like you can never catch a break.
^A new customer moved into your quadarant. I'm making some calls to make sure no one else can move in after this.
^You've got your work cut out for you as is. Between dodging rocks, stars and black holes, now you've got four customers to meet the demands of.
^You pull this off and I'll put in a good word for you. Try to get you a promotion or something. Even though you've been with us 8 days, you work harder than most would on this job.
^Keep it up, Zip. See you at the end of your shift.
